cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on learning distributed representations of words and phrases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses autoencoders for learning these representations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves training neural networks to learn these representations, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis of word co-occurrence, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the quality of the learned representations on several tasks, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
